{
  "texts": [
    "We consider this question, alongside an empirical proposal, in the remainder of the paper.",
    "A caveat about types of AIsWhen discussing human-AI relational norms, it is crucial to distinguish between different types and capabilities of AI systems.",
    "Our research program focuses primarily on AI systems capable of simulating or performing roles traditionally performed only by humans.",
    "This excludes many current AI applications, such as music recommendation algorithms which, while technically AI, do not engage in complex social interactions that would invoke relational norms (however, see [12], for discussion).",
    "Empirical proposalWhether, or to what extent, people apply human-human relational norms towards human-AI relationships is first and foremost an empirical question."
  ]
}